				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">&quot;Bards are only good for DPS and Haste&quot;<a name="55872"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 10 04 10:27 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>When I logged in last night, it was just a few minutes too late to hook up with my normal LDON buddies. They had already assembled a full group and said that they were heading out. I told them to catch me for the next one. So I took off over to Dulak to get some easy EXP while they were running their adventure.
<br />

<br />
About 20 minutes later I start receiving a string of whines from them about how bad the bard they had gotten stuck with was. Normally when I hear bad bard stories its either a bard that overpulls too often, or doesn't want to do anything but play mana song. However this one was a little difference.
<br />

<br />
This bard (who was level 46):
<br />
- Refused to be the puller
<br />
- Would not mez cause his wind instrument skill was &lt; 50
<br />
- Did not twist, only played the haste song (no slows, no damage shield, no AC buffs, nothing but haste).
<br />
- Told the group that bards were only good for Haste and DPS
<br />

<br />
So the group wiped. They then told the bard he was either going to have to start pulling or they were going to boot him from the group. So he does start pulling, but can't mez on overpulls of course, leaving the poor Necro doing crowd control.
<br />

<br />
They lose the adventure and go back to BB for the split, and the bard is immediately disbanded and I replace him. We go back and do a hard and get through the 52 slaughters with 20 minutes to spare.
<br />

<br />
Apparently, the bard who had been in the group first was a twink who had been powerleveled to 40 or so. He had no idea of what the class is about, and didn't really seem to want to learn. 
<br />

<br />
It makes me /boggle when people are like this. Believe it or not, but I actually refuse powerlevelling from my guildies for any of my toons for exactly this reason. Unless you go through the lower levels learning the ropes of your class, then its highly irresponsible to throw yourself into a higher level group.  I do believe that EQ is about having fun. However I also believe that you have some responsibility to know enough about the game and your class so that you are an asset to any group you join. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Menuvian Spiritsong
52 Bard on Prexus <Azure Sky>
</span></td>
