				<td colspan="2"><span>Most classes you can muddle thru if your pl'd but the bard class is unlike any other class.  I don't know about others but since my bard was my first character - I can play other classes fairly well if needed.  
<br />

<br />
With the bonus(ZEM) of leveling in so many zones - you could take a level 1 monk and pl him to 50 in about 24 hours.  got bored 1 weekend.  This takes away a lot of the honing skills people pickup when learning to play the game let alone their class.
<br />

<br />
examples:
<br />
I know many people who just can't /target &lt;name&gt; to group people or can't get across a zone even with a map.
<br />

<br />
I feel for the frustration your friends had when having to deal with people like this.  But lets face it there are a lot of these folks out there.
<br />

<br />
anyways I agree people have to learn about the class they play or it ruins the fun in this game.
