				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: &quot;Bards are only good for DPS and Haste&quot;<a name="56092"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 11 04 11:43 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I feel your pain....
<br />
I could go on about LDoNs forever, I mean I could probably type out at least 2-3 pages on all the misadventures and morons I've run into, but a few months ago I started looking at pickup groups in a whole new light. I ran into an old old friend of mine (59 shammy) and we decided to pair up and get a group together for a MM adventure. After some tells and the usual shinnanegans, we had 6 people ready to go and the shammy was the only one I knew, the others seemed ominously quiet, but the cleric was chatty. Long story short, the ranger and the rogue pulled and insisted I do not pull since they didn't know me, although they felt safe enough to do a high risk mission (/boggle). The shammy knew I had tons of puilling experience but the argument was over and I wasn't going to make a big deal out of it. They were pulling pairs and the ranger was off-tanking while the warrior took the main target, thus negating my need for mezzes. The ranger said something smartass along the lines of &quot;I bet you feel pretty useless, just play mana song and haste, that's all we need you for anyways.&quot; I bit my tongue as I often do, because I know all it takes is the right situation. My patience paid off because they started pulling 3-4 and things got crazy, we lost the cleric and the rogue. I offered to pull, the answer was a big &quot;no&quot;. Rinse and repeat, they pull 4 and the ranger goes down. Cleric says &quot;maybe I should try pulling?&quot; 
<br />
uhhh..... ok.... don't mind me over here smashing my head into the wall. Shammy says &quot;maybe you guys should let Scam pull, I've done a ton of adventures with him, he knows what he's doing&quot;
<br />
   Long story short I ended up pulling and we coasted to the finish line with 9-10 mins to spare, not too shabby considering.
<br />
   I had a long talk with the shammy about how retarted people are and we started doing a lot more LDoNs together in pickup groups, he convinced me to look at it as a challenge to my group abilities instead of a retarted moron of a speedbump. This changed things for me and I've since taken it as part of my role to foster bad groups into good ones, it certainly has it's frustrations but I've also learned a lot about why people do the stupid things they do. 
<br />
